other_tests.findings: Pathological examination of the skin-biopsy specimen showed an infiltrate of mononuclear cells involving the upper and deep dermis, with a periadnexal pattern, and sparing the epidermis. The infiltrating cells expressed CD68 and lysozyme, and CD117, suggesting cutaneous infiltration by acute monocytic leukemia.
other_tests.changes_over_time: After the initial biopsy, within a few days after the start of therapy, there was noticeable regression of skin lesions, and within a week, they had almost completely resolved.
